<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" data-bs-theme="auto">

<head>
  <%- include('../partials/head-meta') %>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/error.css" />

  <script src="/js/theme.js" defer></script>
  <script type="module" src="/js/page-common.js"></script>
</head>

<body>
  <main>
    <div class="container-main text-center">
      <%- include('../partials/header') %>
      <p class="lead mb-4">A lightweight, open-source, privacy-focused file sharing tool.</p>

      <div id="status-card" class="card shadow-sm border-danger">
        <div class="card-body p-4">
          <div id="icon-container" class="mb-3 text-danger">
            <span class="material-icons-round">https</span>
          </div>

          <h5 class="card-title mb-2" id="status-title">Secure Connection Required</h5>
          <p class="card-text text-body-secondary" id="status-message">
            End-to-end encrypted files can only be downloaded over a secure HTTPS connection.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div id="help-statement" class="text-body-secondary mt-4">
        <strong>Why am I seeing this page?</strong><br>
        <p>The uploader enabled End-to-End Encryption (E2EE) for this file.<br>This page decrypts the file directly in
          your browser using the key in the URL.<br>Nobody else, not even the server, can read the true contents of your
          file.</p>

        <p>Modern browsers only allow the JavaScript Web Crypto API (crypto.subtle) and related secure storage features
          in secure contexts.<br>Because this page is being served over unsecured HTTP, the browser blocks decryption
          and saving of the file.</p>

        <p>If you are the owner of this server, enable HTTPS/TLS (for example via Let's Encrypt or a properly configured
          reverse proxy). Once served over HTTPS the browser will permit the Web Crypto API to decrypt and save the
          file.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <%- include('../partials/footer') %>
</body>

</html>